CopyFleet.document: This API is used to replicate server fleet.
CopyFleet.name: Replicates server fleet

CreateGameServerSession.document: This API is used to create a game server session.
CreateGameServerSession.name: Creates game server session

DeleteTimerScalingPolicy.document: This API (DeleteTimerScalingPolicy) is used to delete a scheduled scaling policy of a fleet.
DeleteTimerScalingPolicy.name: Deleting a scheduled scaling policy

DescribeGameServerSessionDetails.document: This API is used to query the list of game server session details.
DescribeGameServerSessionDetails.name: Queries the list of game server session details

DescribeGameServerSessionPlacement.document: This API is used to query the placement of a game server session.
DescribeGameServerSessionPlacement.name: Queries game server session placement

DescribeGameServerSessions.document: This API is used to query the list of game server sessions.
DescribeGameServerSessions.name: Queries game server session list

DescribeInstanceTypes.document: This API is used to obtain the list of CVM types in the specified region.
DescribeInstanceTypes.name: Obtains the list of CVM types in the specified region

DescribePlayerSessions.document: This API is used to get the list of player sessions.
DescribePlayerSessions.name: Queries player session list

DescribeTimerScalingPolicies.document: This API (DescribeTimerScalingPolicies) is used to query the scheduled scaling policies of a fleet. You can query the policies by `fleetID` or the fleet name. The returned results are paged.
DescribeTimerScalingPolicies.name: Queries the list of scheduled scaling policies

EndGameServerSessionAndProcess.document: This API is used to terminate the game server session and the corresponding process, which is applicable to time-limited protection and no protection.
EndGameServerSessionAndProcess.name: Terminates the game server session and the corresponding process

GetGameServerSessionLogUrl.document: This API is used to get the log URL of a game server session.
GetGameServerSessionLogUrl.name: Gets the log URL of game server session

GetInstanceAccess.document: This API is used to get the credentials required for instance login.
GetInstanceAccess.name: Gets credentials required for instance login

JoinGameServerSession.document: This API is used to join a game server session.
JoinGameServerSession.name: Joins game server session

JoinGameServerSessionBatch.document: This API is used to join game server sessions in batch.
JoinGameServerSessionBatch.name: Joins game server sessions in batch

PutTimerScalingPolicy.document:
This API (PutTimerScalingPolicy) is used to create or update a scheduled scaling policy for a fleet.

If the field `timerID` is filled in, the specified policy will be updated, and if `timerID` is left empty, a new policy will be created.
PutTimerScalingPolicy.name: Creating or updating a scheduled scaling policy

SearchGameServerSessions.document: This API is used to search in the list of game server sessions.
SearchGameServerSessions.name: Searches in game server session list

SetServerReserved.document:
This API (SetServerReserved) is used to mark the exceptional instances as retained for troubleshooting.

`ReserveValue`: specifies whether to retain the instance. Valid values: `0` (do not retain), `1` (retain). Default value: `0`.
SetServerReserved.name: Specifies whether to retain an exceptional instance for troubleshooting

StartGameServerSessionPlacement.document: This API is used to start placing a game server session.
StartGameServerSessionPlacement.name: Starts placing game server session

StopGameServerSessionPlacement.document: This API is used to stop placing a game server session.
StopGameServerSessionPlacement.name: Stops placing game server session

UpdateBucketAccelerateOpt.document: This API (UpdateBucketAccelerateOpt) is used to enable COS global acceleration.
UpdateBucketAccelerateOpt.name: Sets COS global acceleration

UpdateBucketCORSOpt.document: This API (UpdateBucketCORSOpt) is used to configure CORS for COS.
UpdateBucketCORSOpt.name: Sets COS CORS

UpdateGameServerSession.document: This API is used to update a game server session.
UpdateGameServerSession.name: Updates game server session

members.document:
Search filter expression. Valid values:
gameServerSessionName: game session name in `String` type
gameServerSessionId: game session ID in `String` type
maximumSessions: maximum number of player sessions in `Number` type
creationTimeMillis: creation time in milliseconds in `Number` type
playerSessionCount: current number of player sessions in `Number` type
hasAvailablePlayerSessions: whether there is available player session in `String` type. Valid values: true, false
gameServerSessionProperties: game session attributes in `String` type

Expressions in `String` type support = and <> for judgment
Expressions in `Number` type support =, <>, >, >=, <, and <= for judgment

Example:
If FilterExpression takes the value:
playerSessionCount>=2 AND hasAvailablePlayerSessions=true"
It means searching for game sessions that have at least two players and have player sessions available.
If FilterExpression takes the value:
gameServerSessionProperties.K1 = 'V1' AND gameServerSessionProperties.K2 = 'V2' OR gameServerSessionProperties.K3 = 'V3'

it means
searching for game sessions that meets the following game server session attributes
{
    "GameProperties":[
        {
            "Key":"K1",
            "Value":"V1"
        },
        {
            "Key":"K2",
            "Value":"V2"
        },
        {
            "Key":"K3",
            "Value":"V3"
        }
    ]
}
members.name: FilterExpression
